			 DBCC UPDATEUSAGE (Transact-SQL) 

					 
								 11/14/2017 
							 2 minutes to read 
							 
								 Contributors 
								 
											 
											 
								 

					 In this article 
						 THIS TOPIC APPLIES TO: SQL Server (starting with 2008) Azure SQL Database Azure SQL Data Warehouse  Parallel Data Warehouse  Reports and corrects pages and row count inaccuracies in the catalog views. These inaccuracies may cause incorrect space usage reports returned by the sp_spaceused system stored procedure. 
 Transact-SQL Syntax Conventions 
 Syntax 
 DBCC UPDATEUSAGE   
(   { database_name | database_id | 0 }   
    [ , { table_name | table_id | view_name | view_id }   
    [ , { index_name | index_id } ] ]   
) [ WITH [ NO_INFOMSGS ] [ , ] [ COUNT_ROWS ] ]   
 Arguments 
 database_name  |  database_id  | 0 Is the name or ID of the database for which to report and correct space us